The course studies the history, development, and the current situation of the three Baltic states taking into consideration their geographical location and political situation. The course also analyses the history of the three Baltic states from the 18th century until today. The second half of the course studies the society of the Baltic countries: the demographic situation and democracy development, the freedom of media and the health of the civil society.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to provide students with an overview of the history of the Baltic states (Estonia, Latvia, and Lithuania) as well as to analyze the influence of Russia in the region and its traces in the modern societies of the Baltic states.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon completion of the course a student -	knows the most important events in the history of the three Baltic states from the early 18th century to the 21st century; -	analyses the emergence of the Baltic states in the 20th century; -	knows the demographic situation and the structure of the societies of the modern Baltic states; -	knows how democracy works in the Baltic states in the 21st century; -	analyses the trends of the civil society in the Baltic states nowadays; -	understands the influences of the Soviet period on the modern Baltic societies.
